00:24:35.057 --> 00:24:37.017
We're almost there.
You can drop us off there.

00:24:37.226 --> 00:24:40.104
Over there? Yes, I'll drop you off there.

00:24:48.645 --> 00:24:51.907
CINEMA TOWN

00:24:52.433 --> 00:24:54.035
Here we are.

00:24:54.118 --> 00:24:55.870
- Thanks, Mom.
- Thank you!

00:25:00.624 --> 00:25:01.959
Take care.

00:25:02.276 --> 00:25:04.444
Visit our house
when you're free next time.

00:25:04.528 --> 00:25:05.572
I'll cook for you.

00:25:05.779 --> 00:25:07.798
Mom, stop making her uncomfortable.

00:25:07.990 --> 00:25:11.593
What's so uncomfortable with cooking food
for my son's friend? Am I right?

00:25:11.702 --> 00:25:13.220
Of course.

00:25:13.721 --> 00:25:15.014
We're late. You should go.

00:25:15.162 --> 00:25:16.306
All right.

00:25:16.389 --> 00:25:17.891
- Have fun!
- Take care.

00:25:17.975 --> 00:25:19.268
- Okay.
- Bye.

00:25:24.398 --> 00:25:25.691
I can't believe this.

00:25:25.841 --> 00:25:27.484
Why did it have to be my mom's taxi?

00:25:28.193 --> 00:25:30.445
I'm sorry if it was uncomfortable.

00:25:31.513 --> 00:25:32.948
Do I really look like that?

00:25:33.282 --> 00:25:34.283
What?

00:25:34.658 --> 00:25:38.370
Does it look like I was raised
in a loving environment?

00:25:39.647 --> 00:25:40.706
What?

00:25:42.466 --> 00:25:46.211
So far, people have only told me

00:25:46.294 --> 00:25:47.754
that I had a troubled look

00:25:48.614 --> 00:25:50.174
with a shadow on my face.

00:25:50.532 --> 00:25:52.532
What are you talking about?

00:25:52.801 --> 00:25:55.762
Who said that to you? Who?

00:25:58.974 --> 00:26:00.058
Let's get going.

00:26:02.136 --> 00:26:03.228
Okay.

00:26:09.259 --> 00:26:11.259
Jun-seok.

00:26:12.262 --> 00:26:14.717
Gyu-cheol cheated on me.

00:26:14.801 --> 00:26:15.827
Where are you now?

00:26:16.892 --> 00:26:18.892
Okay. I'm on my way there.

00:26:20.312 --> 00:26:22.147
Come on. Stop crying.

00:26:37.721 --> 00:26:40.098
Now, Ms. Yun Seol-ha,

00:26:40.474 --> 00:26:44.103
which do you value more?
Your career or your personal life?

00:26:44.294 --> 00:26:46.521
I value my career more.

00:26:48.048 --> 00:26:49.775
Do you really?

00:26:50.926 --> 00:26:53.053
- Why?
- So, when we're on a date,

00:26:53.136 --> 00:26:54.947
you're going to leave me
if something comes up?

00:26:55.531 --> 00:26:57.742
Min-gi, this is supposed to be
a job interview.

00:26:57.825 --> 00:26:58.976
Oh, you're right.

00:26:59.059 --> 00:27:00.311
- Here you go.
- Calm down.

00:27:00.394 --> 00:27:02.580
- Thank you.
- That looks tasty. Thank you.

00:27:03.914 --> 00:27:05.124
Why? Did she say no?

00:27:05.707 --> 00:27:06.958
She has plans that day.

00:27:07.125 --> 00:27:09.044
Really? That's bad news.

00:27:09.361 --> 00:27:11.004
Are you sure you'll be fine on your own?

00:27:11.405 --> 00:27:12.504
What is it?

00:27:12.588 --> 00:27:14.616
Are you trying to find someone
to cover for you on that day?

00:27:14.699 --> 00:27:16.551
- I'll fill in for you.
- Seriously?

00:27:16.718 --> 00:27:17.677
You're free that day?

00:27:17.860 --> 00:27:20.322
What's the point of having a boyfriend?

00:27:20.748 --> 00:27:23.392
You can always ask me
if you need to move heavy things.

00:27:23.475 --> 00:27:26.270
I'm stronger than I look.

00:27:27.171 --> 00:27:28.355
See?

00:27:28.438 --> 00:27:31.050
Min-gi just knows what to say.

00:27:31.133 --> 00:27:32.234
Give me a kiss.

00:27:32.593 --> 00:27:34.987
- Come on.
- You're a lifesaver. Thanks, Min-gi.

00:27:35.095 --> 00:27:38.365
Baby, don't worry a thing about that.
Just focus on the interview.

00:27:38.448 --> 00:27:41.076
- All right, honey?
- Yes, honey.

00:27:41.159 --> 00:27:42.911
You can leave us alone now.
I need to practice for my interview.

00:27:42.994 --> 00:27:45.956
All right.
We don't have time to joke around.

00:27:46.398 --> 00:27:48.751
- Okay.
- Moving on to the next question.

00:27:49.418 --> 00:27:52.713
What has been the most difficult challenge
in your life,

00:27:52.796 --> 00:27:54.798
and how did you overcome it?

00:27:59.136 --> 00:28:00.346
Last night?

00:28:01.513 --> 00:28:03.557
Min-gi, wait!

00:28:03.640 --> 00:28:05.100
I'm joking!

00:28:05.538 --> 00:28:07.419
I have to stop here, right?

00:28:07.503 --> 00:28:09.503
- Yes. And then...
- I lock it here.

00:28:09.586 --> 00:28:12.232
- Okay. I got it.
- Right here.

00:28:12.674 --> 00:28:14.484
- What about my legs? Just one foot?
- Forward.

00:28:14.567 --> 00:28:16.386
- Like that. And do this.
- Okay.

00:28:16.469 --> 00:28:18.071
Oh, right. I always forget.

00:28:18.305 --> 00:28:20.582
- Right?
- Why do I keep forgetting?

00:28:20.665 --> 00:28:22.665
I just can't get this right.

00:28:22.810 --> 00:28:24.120
I just can't.

00:28:24.203 --> 00:28:25.983
Hey, Yeon-jeong.

00:28:26.067 --> 00:28:27.689
Chae-yeong!

00:28:27.772 --> 00:28:31.501
What's up with you, girl?

00:28:34.863 --> 00:28:37.591
- Do you go to clubs together?
- What?

00:28:37.674 --> 00:28:40.010
It's just that you haven't been around.

00:28:40.227 --> 00:28:41.803
Stay out of this.

00:28:42.830 --> 00:28:44.640
You're drunk, aren't you? That's cute.

00:28:46.975 --> 00:28:50.604
